<a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhurk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hurk</a> States:</b><br>
well lets see... the real problem i see with druids from the cleric perspective is not utility, as you have that, and not really buffing, as you have that, but what do you do when the fight starts. Though a single target potg is in order.<br>
<br>
nuking: druid nukes and dots are not the be all end all DPS that wizards kick out. However they are quite good, so i dont see a reason to add here. the fact that dots stop at 52 is similer to clerics not getting direct heals post 53. yes the spell line should be extended near 60, not sure of the power level though, so i make no suggestions. ability to cast magic,fire,ice is your balance here.<br>
<br>
healing: druids get the largest single target heal. it casts 1 second slower than divine light, and takes 50 more mana. The problem here isnt druids missing a heal ability, its the entire game being balanced on the level 39 cleric spell complete heal. Druids should not get group healing, this isnt a line you need, and is one of the rare cleric specific line (pals being clr hybrids get it). All classes should get a level 59-60 3000 point healing spell with about a 6 second cast time. This is to balance the huge disparity of healing between CH and all else.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is that shaman and druids should get complete heal at level 59, with a casting cost of 500.<br>
<br>
Luclin transports: It is intentional that you do not have luclin ability. This is a "method of play" change from VI. Much like the keyed ports to velious. your ports, if and when, will be added after they feel that luclin is thoughly explored. Dont expect them before Vex Thal is entered. After that, expect to get 2 ports to luclin, probly to shadweavers and twilight.<br>
<br>
please dont ask for better healing than clerics get, its petty. Its bad enough the entire class is balanced on one spell. Also dont ask for healing on click items. its bad enough some exsist. for your epic, i would ask for a diseased based snare that lasts 5 minutes, and a cast time of 3 seconds. Other upgrades would be a level 50+ harmony with a much larger radius.<br>
<br>
~Hurk, yes im a cleric. <br>
